verdict: CF Browser Rendering is NOT suitable for inventory extraction from Dutchie menus

workerEndpoint.error: TimeoutError: Navigation timeout of 45000 ms exceeded
workerEndpoint.analysis: Page failed to load within 45s - likely blocked or too slow

directCDP.analysis: CF Browser Rendering does NOT expose CDP externally. The puppeteer binding is internal to the worker only - you cannot connect from outside.
directCDP.limitation: Architectural limitation - CDP is not exposed

dutchieDirectTest.approach: Hit Dutchie embedded menu directly via worker
dutchieDirectTest.analysis: Dutchie returned Cloudflare challenge page - CF Browser Rendering was detected and blocked

limitations.description: CF Browser Rendering binding (env.BROWSER) is internal to worker only. Cannot connect from external clients via CDP WebSocket.
limitations.impact: Cannot use Playwright/Puppeteer from outside the worker

limitations.description: Dutchie uses Cloudflare protection. CF Browser Rendering IPs are detected and challenged.
limitations.impact: Cannot scrape Dutchie menus at all - returns challenge page

limitations.description: External sites (like conbud.com) timeout or fail to load
limitations.impact: Unreliable for scraping sites you don't control

limitations.description: Worker model is stateless request-response. Cannot do multi-step interactions like add-to-cart flows.
limitations.impact: Cannot implement the inventory probing technique (add quantity > error message)

inventory_extraction_feasibility.reason: Site blocked by Cloudflare protection before any scraping possible

recommendations: Use BrowserBase or similar residential proxy browser service (confirmed working)
CF Browser Rendering is designed for your OWN sites, not bypassing protection on external sites
For inventory extraction, need: (1) Residential IP to bypass Cloudflare (2) Interactive session for add-to-cart probing

cost_analysis.recommendation: Worth paying for BrowserBase since CF doesn't work for this use case
